The paper deals with the problem of generalized zero-shot learning, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The proposed approach involves the use of generative adversarial networks (GANs) and semantic features, which are also relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and natural language processing (cs.CL). Finally, the paper mentions the synthesis of visual representations, which falls under multimedia (cs.MM).
